window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The best-selling memoir that's \"irresistible....A kind of Bridget Jones meets </b><b><i>The French Chef</i></b><b>\" (</b><b><i>Philadelphia Inquirer</i></b><b>) that inspired </b><b><i>Julie &amp; Julia</i></b><b>, the major motion picture directed by Nora Ephron, starring Amy Adams as Julie and Meryl Streep as Julia.&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></p> <p>Nearing 30 and trapped in a dead-end secretarial job, Julie Powell reclaims her life by cooking every single recipe in Julia Child's legendary <i>Mastering the Art of French Cooking</i> in the span of one year. It's a hysterical, inconceivable redemptive journey - life rediscovered through aspics, calves' brains and creme brulee.&nbsp;</p> <p>\"A rippingly funny confessional...Diaries do not get any better than this.\" (<i>Texas Monthly</i>)&nbsp;</p>"; 
